    "id": "ipsec"
  }, "IPsec"), mdx("p", null, "IPsec is a de-facto standard in the industry. Once you set the tunnel up, the performance is rather good. IPsec design and building blocks are entirely open and free to read through a set of RFCs. Written mostly by academia, it has a perfect separation of layers \u2014 for example, key exchange (", mdx("a", _extends({
